        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 27 at 6:16PM CDT until July 27 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by earlier heavy thunderstorms continues,
although the heaviest rain has ended.

* WHERE...A portion of northeast Illinois, including the following
counties, Cook, DuPage and Kane.

* WHEN...Until 700 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Creeks and streams may rise out of their banks. Flooding
may occur in poor drainage and urban areas. Underpasses may be
flooded. Roads and streets may be flooded.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 614 PM CDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated between 1 and 3 inches of rain fell from earlier
heavy thunderstorms, with localized amounts a little over 3
inches just west of Bartlett.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Elgin, Bartlett, Streamwood, Carol Stream, Hanover Park,
Addison, St. Charles, West Chicago, Roselle, Bloomingdale,
South Elgin, Wood Dale, Itasca, Gilberts, West Dundee, Sleepy
Hollow, Wayne and Valley View.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>A Flood Advisory means minor flooding along waterways and other poor
drainage areas is imminent or may already be occurring. Persons in
the advisory area should use caution and avoid flood waters.</instruction>
